OL,3,CAdams v BBC jury 'not expected to
OL,4,Cdeliberate for long'
OL,6,FHe continued by giving an overview of
OL,7,Fthe evidence of the main journalist in
OL,8,Fthe programme, Jennifer O'Leary, whom
OL,9,Fhe said was the most important witness
OL,10,Ffor the BBC's defence on fair and
OL,11,Freasonable publication, and for the
OL,12,Fcase that the broadcast was in the
OL,13,Fpublic interest.
OL,15,FMr Owens told the jury he was going to
OL,16,Fgo through the evidence as "quickly as
OL,17,Fpossible", comparing his summary to
OL,18,Fthe pace of the Grand National horse
OL,19,Frace.
OL,26,@xD@\OUyD@IO]
