OL,4,Cdeliberate for long'
OL,6,FExplaining his reasoning for giving a
OL,7,F"fairly detailed" recount of the
OL,8,Fevidence, he said the "smoke of
OL,9,Fbattle" of adversarial cross-
OL,10,Fexamination had now lifted and there
OL,11,Fwas an opportunity for them to rehear
OL,12,Fthe evidence in a calmer, more relaxed
OL,13,Fatmosphere with a fuller appreciation
OL,14,Fof all the issues in the case.
OL,26,@oD@AOUoD@QO]pD@WOUqD@GO]
