OL,3,CAdams v BBC jury 'not expected to
OL,4,Cdeliberate for long'
OL,6,FOn Ms O'Leary's evidence, Mr Owens
OL,7,Fsaid the jury may consider whether it
OL,8,Fproves that that materials she
OL,9,Fgathered from her sources were
OL,10,F"sufficiently robust" to support the
OL,11,Fjournalistic decision to include the
OL,12,Fallegation made by Martin in the
OL,13,Fprogramme.
OL,15,FMs O'Leary and the BBC have said that
OL,16,Fthe central allegation against Mr
OL,17,FAdams had been corroborated by five
OL,18,Fother sources, although this was not
OL,19,Freferenced in the broadcast.
OL,26,@rD@AOUrD@UO]
